    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning kinda yellow and pale compared to the top ones. what's probably going on with them?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your tomato plants are likely suffering from nitrogen deficiency, which causes older leaves to yellow before new growth. This happens because plants prioritize nutrients for the top leaves, leaving the bottom ones to wither. You can fix this by applying a slow-release nitrogen fertilizer or compost around the base of the plants. However, if the yellowing is accompanied by strange spots or wilting, it could also be a sign of root rot or a fungal disease. It's important to check the soil moisture and ensure good drainage to prevent further issues.",
