    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "got it. so if i do the test and the pH is way off, what's the first thing i should do to fix it? i'm worried about making it worse if i just dump stuff in the dirt.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the pH is off, your first step is to mix in a small amount of the corrective agent—like lime for high pH or sulfur for low pH—directly into the top few inches of soil around the plant rather than dumping it all at once. You should water it in gently to help the chemicals settle without shocking the roots, and then wait at least two weeks before re-testing. This slow approach prevents you from accidentally burning the plant or creating a toxic environment if you apply too much too quickly. Once the pH stabilizes, your nitrogen fertilizer will finally be able to work properly.",
